5000|$|The formal {{style for}} <b>life</b> <b>peers</b> is [...] "The Rt Hon the Lord/Lady X" [...] or [...] "Firstname, Lord/Lady X" [...] though women <b>life</b> <b>peers</b> often use [...] "Firstname, Baroness X" [...] to emphasise that they hold a peerage {{in their own}} right. In these examples, X is the title {{in one of the}} forms {{discussed}} above. <b>Life</b> <b>peers</b> who have achieved wide fame under their original name, such as the actor Laurence Olivier, are often incorrectly referred to as Lord/Lady Firstname Lastname after their ennoblement.|$|R
